<HEAD>Navy Pilot Killed in Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A U.S. Navy pilot was killed when the
jet fighter he was flying crashed into a mountain during a training
flight out of Subic Naval Base, the Navy said today.
   A statement identified the pilot as Lt. j.g. Richard E.
Armbruster, 28, a native of Cedar City, Utah, and veteran of the
1983 invasion of the Caribbean island nation of Grenada.
   The statement said search teams found the wreckage of
Armbruster's A-4E Skyhawk aircraft on Wednesday, one day after it
failed to return to Subic's Cubi Point Naval Air Station.
   Cause of the crash has not been determined, the statement said.
   Armbruster was U.S. Army Cobra helicopter pilot decorated for
flying missions during the Grenada invasion. He later transferred to
the U.S. Navy, the statement said.
   A memorial service was scheduled to be held on the base on
Friday, the statement said. Armbruster is survived by his wife,
Sandra.
