<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0445</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Drench Pennsylvania, South</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Heavy rains fell across central Pennsylvania and parts of the
South early today.
   Parts of east-central and south-central Pennsylvania were under a
flood watch early today as showers and thunderstorms brought locally
heavy rain. More than 2 inches drenched the Bedford area during a
two-hour period late Wednesday.
   More than 2 inches of rain also fell in northwest Stueben County
in south-central New York. A flood watch was in effect for parts of
south-central New York today.
   Showers and thunderstorms moved across the central Appalachians
and dumped 2\ inches of rain at Philippi, W.Va. This area of
thunderstorms moved into the Washington area early today.
   Another area of thunderstorms extended from northern Georgia
across parts of Alabama, Mississippi and southern Louisiana to
southeast Texas. Almost an inch of rain fell in Houston in 35
minutes during a thunderstorm.
   Elsewhere, thunderstorms were widely scattered across parts of
New Mexico and Arizona Wednesday evening. Skies were clear this
morning over most of the Great Plains and the northern and central
Rockies. Partly cloudy skies were over the West Coast and Florida
and the Georgia and Carolina coast.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
on the East Coast, the Appalachians, the Ohio and Tennessee valleys,
the Gulf Coast, the lower Great Lakes, the lower half of the
Mississippi Valley and southeast Texas; and widely scattered
thunderstorms in the mountains of the West, especially in Arizona.
   Predicted highs: 70s in the middle Mississippi Valley, the Great
Lakes, the Ohio Valley, New England and the Pacific Coast; 100s in
parts of southwest Texas, eastern Montana, interior valleys of
California and the desert Southwest; and 80s and 90s elsewhere.
   The nation's temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 47 degrees at
Houlton, Maine to 100 at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 73 cloudy; Boston 70 partly cloudy; Buffalo 65
showers; Charleston, S.C. 75 fair; Cincinnati 67 foggy; Cleveland 68
showers; Detroit 66 thunderstorms; Miami 81 fair; New York 68 party
cloudy; Philadelphia 70 cloudy; Pittsburgh 67 foggy; Portland, Maine
63 foggy; Washington 75 thunderstorms.
   _Central: Bismarck 65 fair; Chicago 68 rain; Dallas-Fort Worth 74
fair; Denver 67 fair; Des Moines 62 fair; Indianapolis 67 foggy;
Kansas City 65 partly cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 66 fair;
Nashville 68 fair; New Orleans 79 partly cloudy; St. Louis 65 rain.
   _West: Albuquerque 69 cloudy; Anchorage 56 rain; Las Vegas 94
fair; Los Angeles 69 fair; Salt Lake City 77 fair; San Diego 68
fair; San Francisco 58 windy; Seattle 63 partly cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 66 cloudy; Toronto 68 cloudy.
