<HEAD>Baby, Pronounced Dead, Cries Before Undertaker Arrives</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NATCHITOCHES, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A two-pound premature baby who had been
declared dead began crying just moments before a funeral home worker
arrived to pick up her body.
   ``The hair just stood up on the back of my neck. By the time the
funeral home got there, we had her in the nursery and stabilized and
on a respirator,'' said Dr. Lynn Brouilette, the doctor who had
pronounced the baby dead.
   Katina Payton, 17, gave birth to the unnamed child about 5 a.m.
Wednesday in Natchitoches Parish Hospital. The baby had trouble
breathing, Brouilette said. He said he spent 20 minutes trying to
resuscitate her before giving up because there was no noticeable
heartbeat.
   The baby was taken to Schumpert Medical Center's neonatal
intensive care unit, where she was in critical condition, a nurse
said.
