<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Hungary-Refugees     07-20 0127</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Hungary-Refugees,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>23 Romanians Returned to Budapest From Austrian Border</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Twenty-three Romanians trying to get to
Vienna without visas refused to leave their railroad car Thursday,
so Austrian border officials sent the entire car back to Budapest,
Hungary's news agency reported.
   The Romanians were on the morning train from Budapest to Vienna,
the MTI news agency said. Austrian authorities have in the past
refused to permit Romanian refugees from Hungary to enter the
country without valid travel documents and visas.
   When the group of Romanians refused to leave, the border
officials unhooked the car from the rest of the train and sent it
back to Budapest, MTI reported.
   Hungary has accepted thousands of refugees from neighboring
Romania in the past 18 months.
</TEXT>
