<HEAD>British Fighter Jet Crashes in Netherlands; No Injuries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERGEN, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Royal Air Force Tornado jet crashed
in a field in the Netherlands shortly after takeoff from its West
German base on Thursday, but the two crewmen ejected safely, police
said.
   The British jet hit the ground about two miles outside the
eastern Dutch village of Bergan, according to a police spokesman.
   The cause of the accident was still unknown, the spokesman said,
adding that the twin-engine fighter plane had just taken off from
the nearby RAF base at Laarbruch in West Germany.
