<HEAD>Official Suggests Carter Observe Election</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Bush administration official suggested on
Thursday that former President Carter might go privately to observe
the election for an independent government in Namibia, in southwest
Africa.
   Herman J. Cohen, assistant secretary of State for Africa, noted
that Carter observed the recent election in Panama. The Namibian
