<FIRST>r a AM-Obit-Treen     07-20 0228</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Treen,0234</SECOND>
<HEAD>`It's a Wonderful Life' Character Actress Dies At 82</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEWPORT BEACH, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Character actress Mary Treen, whose
credits over more than three decades included ``It's a Wonderful
Life,'' died Thursday. She was 82.
   Miss Treen died of cancer about 1 a.m. at the home she shared
with Marge Klein, 81, her vaudeville partner and lifelong friend,
said Suzanne Catlin, Ms. Klein's daughter.
   Miss Treen appeared in more than 40 films, including ``Babbitt''
in 1934, ``The Birds and the Bees'' in 1956 and ``Who's Minding the
Store?'' in 1963. In ``It's a Wonderful Life,'' the 1947 film
starring Jimmy Stewart that has become a Christmas film classic, she
played the cousin.
   Born in St. Louis in 1907, Miss Treen studied dancing and
appeared in stage musicals and vaudeville revues before starting her
film career. Ms. Catlin said her mother and Miss Treen used to have
a comedy, singing and dancing act.
   Miss Treen often worked in film comedies and was frequently cast
as a plain-looking working girl.
   She was bedridden for the last year and a half because of hip
replacement surgery and the fracture of her other hip, Ms. Catlin
said. A hospital visit for hip treatment about six weeks ago
revealed the cancer, first detected in her lungs, she said.
   Miss Treen had no children and is survived only by distant
cousins.
</TEXT>
