<HEAD>Savings Bonds Hit $623 Billion in June</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U.S. Savings Bonds posted $623 million in sales
in June, their highest level for the month since 1986, the Treasury
Department reported. However, the total was down from May's sales of
$695 million.
   The department said Wednesday that sales of $5.97 billion during
the first nine months of the fiscal year ending Sept. 30 were 7
percent above sales during that period in fiscal 1988. It estimated
that nearly $8 billion in Savings Bonds will have been sold by the
end of September, compared with $7.26 billion in fiscal 1988.
   The government raised the interest rate on bonds to 7.81 percent
from 7.35 percent on May 1. The new rate is effective through Oct.
31.
