<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Chemicals     07-20 0204</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Chemicals,0213</SECOND>
<HEAD>Record Sales Boost Dow Chemical Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIDLAND, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Record second-quarter sales boosted
quarterly earnings 16.7 percent at Dow Chemical Co., the company
said Thursday.
   Dow said after-tax income rose to $728 million, or $4.04 a share,
from $624 million, or $3.29 a share, in 1988's second quarter.
   Sales grew to $4.60 billion for the three months ended June 30,
the highest ever for a quarter, up about 8 percent from $4.25
billion in the second quarter of last year.
   The previous record for quarterly sales was $4.49 billion in the
first quarter of 1989.
   Dow said its sales of chemicals, plastics and other items
increased 11 percent in Europe, 9 percent in the United States and 4
percent in the rest of the world.
   For the first six months of the year, the Midland, Mich.-based
chemicals company reported income of $1.47 billion, or $8.12 a
share, on sales of $9.09 billion, up from $1.14 billion, or $5.96 a
share, on sales of $8.23 billion in the first half of 1988.
   Dow reported increases in all business segments including
chemicals, plastics, consumer specialties such as Ziploc plastic
bags and performance products such as plastic-lined pipe and
absorbent material for diapers.
</TEXT>
