   MAI Basic Four Inc., spurned in its effort
to buy all of Prime Computer Inc., offered Thursday to purchase
Prime's minicomputer business for $450 million in cash and $150
million of MAI securities.
   Prime Chairman David J. Dunn said its board of directors would
meet to consider the offer.
